Harvard Pilgrim Health Care is currently seeking highly motivated individuals to join our team as the  Director of Clinical Innovation.  The  Director of Clinical Innovation  is responsible for identifying innovative opportunities that reinforce our reputation as an innovation leader and commitment to health equity and Behavioral Health. The position will be responsible for prospecting, selecting, leading, and executing clinical innovation initiatives related to a wide variety of opportunities for clinical innovation, some of which include innovative behavioral health solutions, artificial intelligence, digital therapeutics, and social determinants of health. 
 
 WHAT YOU WILL BE DOING: 
 Responsible for developing the strategy that aligns with goals of Combined Org and guide decisions regarding which opportunities serve broader organizational goals. 
 Lead the development of the business case for new partnerships and projects. 
 Stay abreast of external developments in industry, including but not limited to 1) engaging with local, regional and national trade associations, 2) reviewing emerging literature in this rapidly changing area, 3) be aware of competitor activity 
 Generate, ideate and assess opportunities within the domain, and prioritize those which merit pursuits. Work with the other domain leads to develop and maintain a roadmap of all potential Clinical Innovation partnerships to maintain a growing and diversified pipeline. 
 Accountable for leading execution, managing throughout lifecycle of initiative, overseeing analysis and final evaluation, including decision whether to embed in core Combined Org offerings. Ensure initiatives are properly designed to ensure capable of demonstrating the desired outcome and stay within budget. 
 Seek out opportunities for collaboration resulting in funded projects with the Harvard Pilgrim Institute. 
 Lead role to conduct due diligence and drive execution of contracts and related business agreements. 
 Be known internally across Combined Org as in-house expert and ensure that LOBâ€™s aware of initiatives and understand how they support their business objectives 
 Reinforce and expand HPHC national reputation as industry thought leader 
 
 Qualifications 
WHAT YOU NEED: 
 Masterâ€™s degree and 7-10 years of relevant business experience required, including developing and deploying strategy: clinical degree (RN, pharmacist or more advanced degree) preferred. 
 Previous experience vetting, introducing and implementing innovation programs and solutions required. 
 Experience in and the ability to discern clinical benefits, direct financial benefits and potential benefits of innovative vendor proposals required. 
 Contracting experience required. 
 Resilient, collaborative, flexible, innovative. 
 
